{"key":"processedPost-11574006","value":{"id":11574006,"first":11563000,"last":11574307,"when":1259821690,"utime":"12/03/09 08:28 AM","content":"Anastomosis isn't always a bad thing.&nbsp; However, if you have a few dozen petri dishes and want to do a series of strain isolations, transfer as many sections of the original germinated mycelium as you can to new dishes, and then when stones form, transfer those to new dishes to isolate a good sclerotia producing strain.<br />RR","title":"Re: Sclerotia Strains and Isolation","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}